                    <li class="list-group-item px-5"><h5>Choose a broad spectrum sunscreen that protects against both UVA and UVB radiation. Make sure it is water resistant and has a SPF of 30 or higher. Other sunscreens may help keep you from getting sunburned, but they won’t protect against skin cancer.</h5></li>
                    <li class="list-group-item px-5"><h5>Reapply sunscreen every two hours. Reapply every hour if you are swimming or sweating. share on twitter</h5></li>
